LAST WILL AND TESTAMENT OF [Person-1]

My name is [Person-1]. I presently reside in Lauderdale County, Tennessee, and I declare this to be my Last Will and Testament, revoking all prior testamentary instruments. I have two children: [Person-2], born [Date-1], and [Person-3], born [Date-2].
ARTICLE I

data.text: 1.1 Appointment of Personal Representative. I appoint [Person-2] as Executor of my estate. If [Person-2] should be unable or unwilling to serve for any reason, I then appoint [Person-3] as Executor of my estate. These persons and any successor fiduciaries are referred to generally herein as my "personal representative."

data.text: 1.2 Accounting and Inventory of Estate. Unless such is required by applicable state law, I hereby excuse my personal representative from the requirement of filing an accounting or a detailed inventory of my estate in the probate proceedings.

data.text: 1.3 Bond is Excused. I direct that each personal representative or Executor named herein be permitted to serve without bond. If the law should require a bond for such personal representative or Executor, I then authorize such bond to be purchased using funds of my estate.
